Articles.Content:
On 5/19/2018 at 9:17 AM, FreeThinker said:

Version 1.9.2 for Kerbal Space Program 1.4.3 can be downloaded from here

Released on 2018-05-19

 

I just installed this after getting back into the game after a very long hiatus. I have a fresh install of KSP on Steam, using version 1.9.2. None of my reactors besides the green fission reactor are producing any decent amount of power. When I try to run a thermal turbojet on the magnetized target fusion reactor it doesn't produce even a single kN of thrust, it just says reactor heating insufficient, reduce load blah blah. I did some searching and found the thing about near future electrical, but I never even installed that mod! I don't know what's going on that would cause this to happen.
@nonono The only way to get this effect is if you install the mod somehow on the wrong location. THe WArpPlugin folder need to be put inside the GameData folder

56 minutes ago, FreeThinker said:

@nonono The only way to get this effect is if you install the mod somehow on the wrong location. THe WArpPlugin folder need to be put inside the GameData folder

I went to make sure it was in the right spot and it most certainly was. I even reinstalled the mod after deleting the warp plugin folder and I still get that issue.

I completely reinstalled the game, deleting all the mods I had in the game data folder so I'm back to a clean installation. I installed tweak scale, heat control, and KSPIE, I am still getting the issue where reactors aren't doing anything like they are supposed to.
@nonono Well then there has to be something else. Could you provide you logs?
I would be happy to, I just don't know how. What do I need to do?

On 6/3/2018 at 10:56 PM, FreeThinker said:

@nonono Well then there has to be something else. Could you provide you logs?

Still not sure how to provide the logs you need. Been tinkering with some things in the meantime, even the fission reactors don't work right. Radiators from the mod don't radiate any heat at all but ones from other mods do. I haven't a clue what's going on.

Edited June 7, 2018 by nonono
Fixing images

On 6/3/2018 at 10:56 PM, FreeThinker said:

@nonono Well then there has to be something else. Could you provide you logs?

I think this is what you needed?

I went reading the log file myself hoping to find something that might clue me in, it kept referencing that community resource pack could not make configuration files for "part". I discovered that the version I had was very old. I guess one of the sites that hosts files is known for having out of date stuff (Kurse I think?) I updated to the correct version and this solved the problem.

I think I have found a bug with the Radial Cryogenic Liquid Fuel Tank X11 that causes phantom acceleration and/or spontaneous disassembly of the craft. 

To recreate: 1. Clean install with only KSPI and hyperedit.

2. Build this ship and tweakscale the X11 to a larger size (decreasing size was not tested).  You MUST tweakscale the X11 for the bug to appear... the standard size appears to work normally.

3. hyperedit into orbit

4.  either burn fuel or use hyperedit to reduce the amount of LH2.  

Using hyperedit to reduce the fuel to 0 causes the command pod to rocket off into space at the speed of light.

I discovered the bug in my main game which has 50+ mods in it.  My ship in that version has several X11s of different sizes and most of my troubleshooting actually happened with that ship.  It appears that once a tweakscaled X11 has it's fuel reduced to about 50%, the phantom forces appear.  The closer to 0 it gets, the greater the acceleration.  It also appeared that the effect is amplified when the X11 is tweakscaled to larger and larger sizes.  Rapidly emptying many scaled X11s is a down and dirty way to exceed the speed of light haha.
